The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 ICC rejects referrals trial

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: The ICC on Thursday rejected a recommendation to allow players three appeals per innings to the TV umpire on a trial basis at this years Champions Trophy (as reported in Thursdays Late City edition). 

It was previously suggested that the players could appeal to the TV umpire in case they were dissatisfied with the on-field umpires decision. 

The CEC also approved a series of recommendations concerning the issue of bad light and agreed to the increased use of light meters. 

The following appointments have been made: 

Executive Board 

H.R.H. Tunku Imran (Malaysia),

Stanley Perlman (Israel), Samir Inamdar (Kenya). 

Chief Executives Committee 

Ricardo Lord (Argentina)

John Cribbin (Hong Kong)

Laurie Pieters (Namibia). 




